SUMMARY:Back To School Health Clinic - Central
LOCATION:4401 N. Himes Ave. Tampa \, FL 33614 United States
DESCRIPTION:The Back-2-School Health Clinics are returning this summer to 
 help families across Hillsborough County prepare for the new school year. 
 The clinics provide no-cost school physicals\, routine immunizations\, and
  Florida Form DH 680 immunization record transfersservices that are essent
 ial for school enrollment. A non-refundable 10 registration fee is require
 d per family (not per child). Medical services are available by appointmen
 t only for children who are uninsured\, underinsured\, or enrolled in Medi
 caid. The clinics are designed to serve students entering Kindergarten\, e
 ntering 7th grade\, or those who are NEW to Hillsborough County Public or 
 Charter Schools in any grade level. Clinics will be held every Saturday fr
 om July 11 through August 8\, 2026\, at six convenient locations throughou
 t Hillsborough County. Space is limited\, and walk-ins cannot be accommoda
 ted. Families are encouraged to register early at www.b2shc.org. Start the
  school year strong by ensuring your child is healthy\, protected\, and re
 ady to learn! \n\nPermalink: https://www.tampa.gov/node/192026
URL;VALUE=URI:https://www.tampa.gov/node/192026
END:VEVENT
